
.TH task1 1 "December 2025" "OS Tasks" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
task1 \- File Manager for basic filesystem operations
.SH SYNOPSIS
task1
.SH DESCRIPTION
The File Manager provides a menu-driven interface to:
.IP \[bu] 2
List files and directories
.IP \[bu] 2
Change permissions of files/directories
.IP \[bu] 2
Create and delete files/directories
.IP \[bu] 2
Create symbolic link files
It is part of the OS Tasks project and is invoked via the main program.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B List files/directories
Prompts for a path and displays entries with type and permissions.
.TP
.B Change permissions
Prompts for path and numeric mode (e.g., 755) and applies chmod.
.TP
.B Create file/directory
Creates a new file (touch) or directory (mkdir).
.TP
.B Delete file/directory
Deletes a file or a directory (recursively for directories with confirmation).
.TP
.B Create symbolic link
Creates a symlink at the specified link name pointing to the target.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
os_tasks        # run main menu
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
ls(1), chmod(1), ln(1), rm(1), mkdir(1)
